### 5.2 PROCUREMENT OFFICER — DASHBOARD

#### Layout: Three-Column (permanent)
```
[Icon rail] | [Main canvas] | [Live panel]
```

**Left Rail — Navigation**
```
[VENDORA logo]
────────────────
[LayoutDashboard]   Dashboard
[FileText]          RFQs
[Building2]         Vendors
[GitCompare]        Compare
[ShoppingCart]      Purchase Orders
[Receipt]           Invoices
[MessageSquare]     Negotiations
────────────────
[Bell]              Notifications (with count badge)
[User]              Profile
```

**Center Canvas:**

*KPI Strip (5 tiles, full width, horizontal row):*

```
[ PENDING APPROVALS ] [ ACTIVE RFQs ] [ POs THIS MONTH ] [ INVOICES PENDING ] [ SAVINGS THIS MONTH ]
       3                    7             ₹14.2L                 5                  ₹2.3L ↑
   ⚠ 1 urgent           2 expiring      +12% MoM             ₹8L value           vs last mo
```

Each tile shows:
- Label
- Value (counts up from 0 on page load)
- Sub-info (urgent count, trend %, etc.)
- Amber progress underline fills toward monthly target

*Procurement Pipeline (below KPIs):*

Horizontal kanban-style columns:
```
RFQ SENT | QUOTES IN | COMPARING | APPROVAL | PO ISSUED | INVOICED
```

Each card within a column shows:
- Item name
- Value in ₹
- Vendor count + countdown `⏰ 3d 4h left`
- Deadlines < 24h: pulsing indicator
- Click any card → detail slide-over opens from right (no page nav)

*Quick Actions (bottom of center canvas):*

Three buttons:
```
[+ CREATE NEW RFQ]   [VIEW ALL POs]   [GENERATE INVOICE]
```

**Right Panel — Live Operations**

```
LIVE ACTIVITY  ●  (pulsing green dot)
──────────────────────────────────

● 2m   Mehta Industries submitted quote for RFQ #2847
● 15m  Manager approved PO #1203 — ₹38,000
● 1h   New vendor: Sharma Traders registered
● 2h   Invoice #INV-089 emailed to Global Supplies
● 3h   RFQ #2851 deadline extended 2 days
```

- New events slide in from top (Framer Motion `AnimatePresence`)
- Supabase realtime subscription updates this feed live
- Scrollable
- Below feed: **Savings Widget** (see Section 5.14)

